org.pikater.core.agents.system

Class Agent_Manager

  • java.lang.Object
    • jade.core.Agent
      • org.pikater.core.agents.PikaterAgent
        • org.pikater.core.agents.system.Agent_Manager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    jade.core.TimerListener, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Runnable

    public class Agent_Manager
extends PikaterAgent
    Agent Manager is a central control unit of the system. It handles requests to compute batches from GUI agents (ParserBehaviour), recommender agents (ParserBehaviour), queries from search agents (receiveQuery behaviour). It also receives the computations' results from Planner agent (ParserBehaviour).

    Klara

      • setup

        protected void setup()
        Initializes Agent_Manager agent.

        Registers manager with yellow pages and starts its three behaviours:

        • ParserBehaviour that deals with requests from GUI agents
        • SubscriptionResponder behaviour (for sending subscriptions messages about the results to registered subscribers)
        • Agent_Manager.ReceiveQuery behaviour that receives queries from search agents
        Overrides:
        setup in class jade.core.Agent

      • sendSubscription

        public void sendSubscription(jade.lang.acl.ACLMessage result,
                    jade.lang.acl.ACLMessage originalMessage)
        A method for sending "subscription" messages about the (partial) computation results to whoever is subscribed to it. Typically the subscriber is a GUI agent.

        Note that it is also possible for an agent to get the results directly from the database, where they are being stored as soon as the single computations are finished. In this case a subscription can be used as a cue that there have been a progress in a processing of a batch.

        Parameters:
        result - the message containing a result of a computation
        originalMessage - the message that the subscriber originally sent to the Manager, used to create a subscription message
